{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm kind of tired of talking about simplicity, actually,"},{"time":3000,"text":"so I thought I'd make my life more complex, as a serious play."},{"time":6000,"text":"So, I'm going to, like, go through some slides \n\n"},{"time":8000,"text":"from way back when,"},{"time":10000,"text":"and walk through them to give you a sense of how I end up here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":13000,"text":"So, basically it all began with \n\n"},{"time":15000,"text":"this whole idea of a computer."},{"time":17000,"text":"Who has a computer? Yeah.\n\n"},{"time":20000,"text":"O.K., so, everyone has a computer."},{"time":22000,"text":"Even a mobile phone, it's a computer. \n\n"},{"time":24000,"text":"And -- anyone remember this workbook, \n\n"},{"time":27000,"text":"\"Instant Activities for Your Apple\" -- \n\n"},{"time":29000,"text":"free poster in each book?"},{"time":31000,"text":"This was how computing began. \n\n"},{"time":33000,"text":"Don't forget: a computer came out; it had no software. \n\n"},{"time":37000,"text":"You'd buy that thing, you'd bring it home, you'd plug it in, \n\n"},{"time":40000,"text":"and it would do absolutely nothing at all. \n\n"},{"time":42000,"text":"So, you had to program it, \n\n"},{"time":44000,"text":"and there were great programming, like, tutorials, like this. \n\n"},{"time":46000,"text":"I mean, this was great. \n\n"},{"time":48000,"text":"It's, like, you know, Herbie the Apple II."},{"time":50000,"text":"It's such a great way to -- \n\n"},{"time":52000,"text":"I mean, they should make Java books like this, \n\n"},{"time":55000,"text":"and we've have no problem learning a program. \n\n"},{"time":57000,"text":"But this was a great, grand time of the computer, \n\n"},{"time":59000,"text":"when it was just a raw, raw, what is it? kind of an era. \n\n"},{"time":63000,"text":"And, you see,\n\n"},{"time":66000,"text":"this era coincided with my own childhood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68000,"text":"I grew up in a tofu factory in Seattle. \n\n"},{"time":71000,"text":"Who of you grew up in a family business, \n\n"},{"time":74000,"text":"suffered the torture? Yes, yes."},{"time":76000,"text":"The torture was good. Wasn't it good torture? \n\n"},{"time":79000,"text":"It was just life-changing, you know. And so, in my life, you know, I was in the tofu; \n\n"},{"time":82000,"text":"it was a family business. \n\n"},{"time":84000,"text":"And my mother was a kind of a designer, also. \n\n"},{"time":87000,"text":"She'd make this kind of, like, wall of tofu cooking, \n\n"},{"time":90000,"text":"and it would confuse the customers, \n\n"},{"time":92000,"text":"because they all thought it was a restaurant."},{"time":94000,"text":"A bad sort of branding thing, or whatever. \n\n"},{"time":96000,"text":"But, anyway, that's where I grew up, \n\n"},{"time":98000,"text":"in this little tofu factory in Seattle, \n\n"},{"time":100000,"text":"and it was kind of like this: \n\n"},{"time":103000,"text":"a small room where I kind of grew up. I'm big there in that picture.\n\n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":106000,"text":"That's my dad. My dad was kind of like MacGyver, really: \n\n"},{"time":109000,"text":"he would invent, like, ways to make things heavy.\n\n"},{"time":112000,"text":"Like back here, there's like, concrete block technology here, \n\n"},{"time":115000,"text":"and he would need the concrete blocks to press the tofu, \n"},{"time":118000,"text":"because tofu is actually kind of a liquidy type of thing, \n\n"},{"time":121000,"text":"and so you have to have heavy stuff \n\n"},{"time":123000,"text":"to push out the liquid and make it hard. \n\n"},{"time":125000,"text":"Tofu comes out in these big batches, \n\n"},{"time":128000,"text":"and my father would sort of cut them by hand. \n\n"},{"time":131000,"text":"I can't tell you -- family business story: you'd understand this -- \n\n"},{"time":134000,"text":"my father was the most sincere man possible. \n\n"},{"time":137000,"text":"He walked into a Safeway once on a rainy day,\n\n"},{"time":140000,"text":"slipped, broke his arm, rushed out:"},{"time":142000,"text":"he didn't want to inconvenience Safeway. \n\n"},{"time":145000,"text":"So, instead, you know, my father's, like, arm's broken \n\n"},{"time":147000,"text":"for two weeks in the store, and that week -- \n\n"},{"time":150000,"text":"now, those two weeks were when my older brother and I \n\n"},{"time":152000,"text":"had to do everything."},{"time":154000,"text":"And that was torture, real torture. \n\n"},{"time":157000,"text":"Because, you see, we'd seen my father \n\n"},{"time":159000,"text":"taking the big block of tofu and cutting it,"},{"time":161000,"text":"like, knife in, zap, zap, zap. We thought, wow. \n\n"},{"time":164000,"text":"So, the first time I did that, I went, like, whoa! Like this. \n\n"},{"time":167000,"text":"Bad blocks. But anyways, \n\n"},{"time":170000,"text":"the tofu to me was kind of my origin, basically."},{"time":174000,"text":"And because working in a store was so hard, \n\n"},{"time":177000,"text":"I liked going to school; it was like heaven. \n\n"},{"time":180000,"text":"And I was really good at school. \n\n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":182000,"text":"So, when I got to MIT, you know, \n\n"},{"time":184000,"text":"as most of you who are creatives,"},{"time":186000,"text":"your parents all told you not to be creative, right? \n\n"},{"time":189000,"text":"So, same way, you know, \n\n"},{"time":191000,"text":"I was good at art and good at math, and my father says, he's --"},{"time":193000,"text":"John's good at math. \n\n"},{"time":195000,"text":"I went to MIT, did my math, \n\n"},{"time":197000,"text":"but I had this wonderful opportunity,"},{"time":199000,"text":"because computers had just become visual. \n\n"},{"time":202000,"text":"The Apple -- Macintosh just came out; \n\n"},{"time":204000,"text":"I had a Mac in hand when I went to MIT. \n\n"},{"time":206000,"text":"And it was a time when a guy who, kind of, \n\n"},{"time":208000,"text":"could cross the two sides --"},{"time":210000,"text":"it was a good time. \n\n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":212000,"text":"And so, I remember that my first major piece of software \n\n"},{"time":215000,"text":"was on a direct copy of then-Aldus PageMaker. \n\n"},{"time":218000,"text":"I made a desktop publishing system way back when, \n\n"},{"time":221000,"text":"and that was, kind of, my first step into figuring out how to -- \n\n"},{"time":224000,"text":"oh, these two sides are kind of fun to mix. \n\n"},{"time":226000,"text":"And the problem when you're younger --\n\n"},{"time":228000,"text":"for all you students out there --"},{"time":230000,"text":"is, your head gets kind of big really easy. \n\n"},{"time":233000,"text":"And when I was making icons, I was, like, \n\n"},{"time":235000,"text":"the icon master,"},{"time":237000,"text":"and I was, like, yeah, I'm really good at this, you know. \n\n"},{"time":239000,"text":"And then luckily, you know, \n\n"},{"time":241000,"text":"I had the fortune of going to something called a library, \n\n"},{"time":244000,"text":"and in the library I came upon this very book. \n\n"},{"time":247000,"text":"I found this book. It's called, \n\n"},{"time":249000,"text":"\"Thoughts on Design,\" by a man named Paul Rand."},{"time":252000,"text":"It's a little slim volume; I'm not sure if you've seen this. \n\n"},{"time":254000,"text":"It's a very nice little book. It's about this guy, Paul Rand, \n\n"},{"time":257000,"text":"who was one of the greatest graphic designers, \n\n"},{"time":259000,"text":"and also a great writer as well. \n\n"},{"time":261000,"text":"And when I saw this man's work, \n\n"},{"time":263000,"text":"I realized how bad I was at design,"},{"time":266000,"text":"or whatever I called it back then, \n\n"},{"time":268000,"text":"and I suddenly had a kind of career goal, \n\n"},{"time":270000,"text":"kind of in hot pursuit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274000,"text":"So I kind of switched. I went to MIT, finished. \n"},{"time":278000,"text":"I got my masters,\nand then went to art school after that.\n\n"},{"time":282000,"text":"And just began to design stuff,"},{"time":284000,"text":"like chopstick wrappers, napkins, menus -- whatever I could get a handle on:\n\n"},{"time":286000,"text":"sort of wheel-and-deal, move up in the design world, whatever. \n\n"},{"time":289000,"text":"And isn't it that strange moment when you publish your design?\n\n"},{"time":292000,"text":"Remember that moment -- publishing your designs? \n\n"},{"time":294000,"text":"Remember that moment? It felt so good, didn't it? \n\n"},{"time":297000,"text":"So, I was published, you know, \n\n"},{"time":298000,"text":"so, wow, my design's in a book, you know? \n\n"},{"time":300000,"text":"After that, things kind of got strange, \n\n"},{"time":302000,"text":"and I got thinking about the computer, \n\n"},{"time":304000,"text":"because the computer to me always, kind of, bothered me. \n\n"},{"time":307000,"text":"I didn't quite get it. And Paul Rand\n\n"},{"time":309000,"text":"was a kind of crusty designer, \n\n"},{"time":312000,"text":"you know, a crusty designer, like a good -- kind of like a good French bread? \n\n"},{"time":315000,"text":"You know, he wrote in one of his books: \n\n"},{"time":317000,"text":"\"A Yale student once said,"},{"time":319000,"text":"'I came here to learn how to design, not how to use a computer.' \n\n"},{"time":322000,"text":"Design schools take heed.\" \n\n"},{"time":324000,"text":"This is in the '80s,\n\n"},{"time":326000,"text":"in the great clash of computer/non-computer people."},{"time":329000,"text":"A very difficult time, actually. \n\n"},{"time":331000,"text":"And this to me was an important message from Rand. \n\n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":335000,"text":"And so I began to sort of mess with the computer at the time. \n\n"},{"time":338000,"text":"This is the first sort of play thing I did, my own serious play. \n\n"},{"time":341000,"text":"I built a working version of an Adobe Illustrator-ish thing. \n\n"},{"time":345000,"text":"It looks like Illustrator; it can, like, draw. \n\n"},{"time":347000,"text":"It was very hard to make this, actually. \n\n"},{"time":349000,"text":"It took a month to make this part. \n\n"},{"time":351000,"text":"And then I thought, what if I added this feature, \n\n"},{"time":353000,"text":"where I can say, this point, \n\n"},{"time":355000,"text":"you can fly like a bird. You're free, kind of thing.\n\n"},{"time":358000,"text":"So I could, sort of, change the kind of stability \n\n"},{"time":362000,"text":"with a little control there on the dial, \n\n"},{"time":364000,"text":"and I can sort of watch it flip around. \n"},{"time":366000,"text":"And this is in 1993. \n"},{"time":369000,"text":"And when my professors saw this, they were very upset at me. \n\n"},{"time":373000,"text":"They were saying, Why's it moving? \n\n"},{"time":376000,"text":"They were saying, Make it stop now."},{"time":379000,"text":"Now, I was saying, Well, that's the whole point: it's moving.\n\n"},{"time":381000,"text":"And he says, Well, when's it going to stop?\n\n"},{"time":383000,"text":"And I said, Never.\n\n"},{"time":384000,"text":"And he said, Even worse. Stop it now.\n\n"},{"time":387000,"text":"I started studying this whole idea, \n\n"},{"time":389000,"text":"of like, what is this computer? It's a strange medium."},{"time":392000,"text":"It's not like print. It's not like video. \n\n"},{"time":395000,"text":"It lasts forever. It's a very strange medium. \n\n"},{"time":398000,"text":"So, I went off with this, \n\n"},{"time":400000,"text":"and began to look for things even more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402000,"text":"And so in Japan, I began to experiment with people. \n\n"},{"time":405000,"text":"This is actually bad: human experiments. \n\n"},{"time":408000,"text":"I would do these things where I'd have students become pens: \n\n"},{"time":411000,"text":"there's blue pen, red pen, green pen, black pen. \n\n"},{"time":414000,"text":"And someone sits down and draws a picture. \n\n"},{"time":422000,"text":"They're laughing because he said, \n\n"},{"time":424000,"text":"draw from the middle-right to the middle, and he kind of messed up.\n\n"},{"time":427000,"text":"See, humans don't know how to take orders; \n\n"},{"time":429000,"text":"the computer's so good at it. \n\n"},{"time":431000,"text":"This guy figured out how to get the computer to draw with two pens at once: \n\n"},{"time":434000,"text":"you know, you, pen, do this, and you, pen, do this."},{"time":437000,"text":"And so began to have multiple pens on the page --"},{"time":440000,"text":"again, hard to do with our hands. \n\n"},{"time":443000,"text":"And then someone discovered this \"a-ha moment\" \n\n"},{"time":445000,"text":"where you could use coordinate systems. \n\n"},{"time":448000,"text":"We thought, ah, this is when it's going to happen. \n\n"},{"time":450000,"text":"In the end, he drew a house. It was the most boring thing. \n\n"},{"time":453000,"text":"It became computerish; we began to think computerish -- \n\n"},{"time":456000,"text":"the X, Y system -- and so that was kind of a revelation. \n\n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":459000,"text":"And after this I wanted to build a computer out of people, \n\n"},{"time":462000,"text":"called a human-powered computer. \n\n"},{"time":464000,"text":"So, this happened in 1993."},{"time":468000,"text":"Sound down, please. \n\n"},{"time":469000,"text":"It's a computer where the people are the parts. \n\n"},{"time":473000,"text":"I have behind this wall a disk drive, a CPU, \n\n"},{"time":477000,"text":"a graphics card, a memory system. \n\n"},{"time":479000,"text":"They're picking up a giant floppy disk made of cardboard. \n\n"},{"time":482000,"text":"It's put inside the computer. \n\n"},{"time":485000,"text":"And that little program's on that cardboard disk. \n\n"},{"time":488000,"text":"So, she wears the disk, \n\n"},{"time":491000,"text":"and reads the data off the sectors of the disk,"},{"time":495000,"text":"and the computer starts up; it sort of boots up, really. \n\n"},{"time":498000,"text":"And it's a sort of a working computer. And when I built this computer,"},{"time":501000,"text":"I had a moment of -- what is it called? -- \n\n"},{"time":503000,"text":"the epiphany where I realized that the computer's just so fast. \n\n"},{"time":507000,"text":"This computer appears to be fast - she's working pretty hard, \n\n"},{"time":511000,"text":"and people are running around, and we think, wow, this is happening at a fast rate.\n\n"},{"time":515000,"text":"And this computer's programmed to do only one thing, which is,\n\n"},{"time":518000,"text":"if you move your mouse, the mouse changes on the screen. \n\n"},{"time":521000,"text":"On the computer, when you move your mouse, that arrow moves around. \n\n"},{"time":525000,"text":"On this computer, if you move the mouse, it takes half an hour \n\n"},{"time":527000,"text":"for the mouse cursor to change. \n\n"},{"time":529000,"text":"To give you a sense of the speed, the scale: \n\n"},{"time":531000,"text":"the computer is just so amazingly fast, O.K.?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":534000,"text":"And so, after this I began to do experiments for different companies.\n\n"},{"time":537000,"text":"This is something I did for Sony in 1996. \n\n"},{"time":540000,"text":"It was three Sony \"H\" devices \n\n"},{"time":542000,"text":"that responded to sound."},{"time":544000,"text":"So, if you talk into the mike,"},{"time":546000,"text":"you'll hear some music in your headphones; \n\n"},{"time":548000,"text":"if you talk in the phone, then video would happen. \n\n"},{"time":550000,"text":"So, I began to experiment with industry in different ways \n\n"},{"time":552000,"text":"with this kind of mixture of skills. \n\n"},{"time":555000,"text":"I did this ad. I don't believe in this kind of alcohol, but I do drink sometimes. \n\n"},{"time":559000,"text":"And Chanel. So, getting to do different projects. \n\n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":561000,"text":"And also, one thing I realized is that \n\n"},{"time":563000,"text":"I like to make things."},{"time":565000,"text":"We like to make things. It's fun to make things. \n\n"},{"time":568000,"text":"And so I never developed the ability to have a staff. \n\n"},{"time":570000,"text":"I have no staff; it's all kind of made by hand -- \n\n"},{"time":572000,"text":"these sort of broken hands."},{"time":574000,"text":"And these hands were influenced \n\n"},{"time":577000,"text":"by this man, Mr. Inami Naomi."},{"time":580000,"text":"This guy was my kind of like mentor. \n\n"},{"time":582000,"text":"He was the first digital media producer in Tokyo. \n\n"},{"time":585000,"text":"He's the guy that kind of discovered me, \n\n"},{"time":587000,"text":"and kind of got me going in digital media. \n\n"},{"time":589000,"text":"He was such an inspirational guy. \n\n"},{"time":592000,"text":"I remember, like, we'd be in his studio, like, at 2 a.m., \n\n"},{"time":595000,"text":"and then he'd show up from some client meeting. \n\n"},{"time":598000,"text":"He'd come in and say, you know, \n\n"},{"time":600000,"text":"If I am here, everything is okay."},{"time":603000,"text":"And you'd feel so much better, you know. \n\n"},{"time":605000,"text":"And I'll never forget how, like, but -- I'll never forget how, like,\n\n"},{"time":609000,"text":"he had a sudden situation with his -- he had an aneurysm. \n\n"},{"time":612000,"text":"He went into a coma."},{"time":614000,"text":"And so, for three years he was out, and he could only blink, \n\n"},{"time":617000,"text":"and so I realized at this moment, I thought, wow --\n\n"},{"time":619000,"text":"how fragile is this thing we're wearing, \n\n"},{"time":621000,"text":"this body and mind we're wearing, \n\n"},{"time":623000,"text":"and so I thought, How do you go for it more? \n\n"},{"time":625000,"text":"How do you take that time you have left and go after it? \n\n"},{"time":628000,"text":"So, Naomi was pivotal in that. \n\n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":630000,"text":"And so, I began to think more carefully about the computer. \n\n"},{"time":633000,"text":"This was a moment where I was thinking about, \n\n"},{"time":635000,"text":"so, you have a computer program, \n\n"},{"time":637000,"text":"it responds to motion -- X and Y -- \n\n"},{"time":641000,"text":"and I realized that each computer program \n\n"},{"time":643000,"text":"has all these images inside the program."},{"time":646000,"text":"So, if you can see here, you know, \n\n"},{"time":648000,"text":"that program you're seeing in the corner,"},{"time":650000,"text":"if you spread it out, it's all these things all at once. \n\n"},{"time":653000,"text":"It's real simultaneity. It's nothing we're used to working with. \n\n"},{"time":657000,"text":"We're so used to working in one vector. \n\n"},{"time":659000,"text":"This is all at the same time."},{"time":661000,"text":"The computer lives in so many dimensions. \n\n"},{"time":663000,"text":"And also, at the same time I was frustrated, \n\n"},{"time":665000,"text":"because I would go to all these art and design schools everywhere, \n\n"},{"time":667000,"text":"and there were these, like, \"the computer lab,\" you know, \n\n"},{"time":670000,"text":"and this is, like, in the late 1990s, \n\n"},{"time":673000,"text":"and this is in Basel,\n"},{"time":675000,"text":"a great graphic design school."},{"time":677000,"text":"And here's this, like, dirty, kind of, shoddy, \n"},{"time":679000,"text":"kind of, dark computer room. \n\n"},{"time":682000,"text":"And I began to wonder, Is this the goal? \n\n"},{"time":684000,"text":"Is this what we want, you know? \n\n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":687000,"text":"And also, I began to be fascinated by machines -- \n\n"},{"time":690000,"text":"you know, like copy machines -- and so this is actually in Basel."},{"time":693000,"text":"I noticed how we spent so much time on making it interactive -- \n\n"},{"time":696000,"text":"this is, like, a touch screen -- \n\n"},{"time":698000,"text":"and I noticed how you can only touch five places, \n\n"},{"time":700000,"text":"and so, \"why are we wasting so much interactivity everywhere?\" \n\n"},{"time":703000,"text":"became a question. And also, the sound: \n\n"},{"time":706000,"text":"I discovered I can make my ThinkPad pretend it's a telephone. \n\n"},{"time":711000,"text":"You get it? No? O.K."},{"time":713000,"text":"And also, I discovered in Logan airport, \n\n"},{"time":716000,"text":"this was, like, calling out to me. \n\n"},{"time":724000,"text":"Do you hear that? It's like cows. This is at 4 a.m. at Logan. \n\n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":727000,"text":"So, I was wondering, like, \n\n"},{"time":729000,"text":"what is this thing in front of me, this computer thing? \n\n"},{"time":732000,"text":"It didn't make any sense. \n\n"},{"time":734000,"text":"So, I began to make things again. This is another series of objects\n"},{"time":736000,"text":"made of old computers from my basement. \n\n"},{"time":738000,"text":"I made -- I took my old Macintoshes \n\n"},{"time":740000,"text":"and made different objects out of them from Tokyo. \n"},{"time":743000,"text":"I began to be very disinterested in computers themselves, \n\n"},{"time":746000,"text":"so I began to make paintings out of PalmPilots. \n\n"},{"time":748000,"text":"I made this series of works. \n\n"},{"time":750000,"text":"They're paintings I made and put a PalmPilot in the middle \n\n"},{"time":753000,"text":"as a kind of display that's sort of thinking, \n\n"},{"time":755000,"text":"I'm abstract art. What am I? I'm abstract.\n\n"},{"time":758000,"text":"And so it keeps thinking out loud of its own abstraction. \n\n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":762000,"text":"I began to be fascinated by plastic, \n\n"},{"time":765000,"text":"so I spent four months making eight plastic blocks \n"},{"time":768000,"text":"perfectly optically transparent, \n\n"},{"time":770000,"text":"as a kind of release of stress."},{"time":773000,"text":"Because of that, I became interested in blue tape, \n\n"},{"time":776000,"text":"so in San Francisco, at C.C., I had a whole exhibition on blue tape."},{"time":779000,"text":"I made a whole installation out of blue tape -- blue painters' tape.\n\n"},{"time":781000,"text":"And at this point my wife kind of got worried about me, \n\n"},{"time":784000,"text":"so I stopped doing blue tape and began to think, \n\n"},{"time":786000,"text":"Well, what else is there in life? \n\n"},{"time":788000,"text":"And so computers, as you know, \n\n"},{"time":791000,"text":"these big computers, there are now tiny computers. \n\n"},{"time":793000,"text":"They're littler computers, so the one-chip computers, \n\n"},{"time":795000,"text":"I began to program one-chip computers \n\n"},{"time":797000,"text":"and make objects out of P.C. boards, LEDs."},{"time":801000,"text":"I began to make LED sculptures \n\n"},{"time":803000,"text":"that would live inside little boxes out of MDF. \n\n"},{"time":806000,"text":"This is a series of light boxes I made for a show in Italy. \n\n"},{"time":810000,"text":"Very simple boxes: you just press one button and some LED interaction occurs. \n\n"},{"time":813000,"text":"This is a series of lamps I made. This is a Bento box lamp: \n\n"},{"time":816000,"text":"it's sort of a plastic rice lamp;"},{"time":819000,"text":"it's very friendly. \n\n"},{"time":821000,"text":"I did a show in London last year made out of iPods -- \n\n"},{"time":824000,"text":"I used iPods as a material. \n\n"},{"time":826000,"text":"So I took 16 iPod Nanos \n\n"},{"time":828000,"text":"and made a kind of a Nano fish, basically."},{"time":830000,"text":"Recently, this is for Reebok. \n\n"},{"time":832000,"text":"I've done shoes for Reebok as well,"},{"time":834000,"text":"as a kind of a hobby for apparel. \n\n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":836000,"text":"So anyways, there are all these things you can do, \n"},{"time":839000,"text":"but the thing I love the most is to \n\n"},{"time":841000,"text":"experience, taste the world."},{"time":843000,"text":"The world is just so tasty. \n\n"},{"time":845000,"text":"We think we'll go to a museum; that's where all the tastes are. \n\n"},{"time":847000,"text":"No, they're all out there. \n\n"},{"time":849000,"text":"So, this is, like, in front of the Eiffel Tower, really,\n\n"},{"time":851000,"text":"actually, around the Louvre area. \n\n"},{"time":853000,"text":"This I found, where nature had made a picture for me. \n\n"},{"time":855000,"text":"This is a perfect 90-degree angle by nature. \n\n"},{"time":857000,"text":"In this strange moment where, like, these things kind of appeared.\n\n"},{"time":860000,"text":"We all are creative people. \n\n"},{"time":862000,"text":"We have this gene defect in our mind."},{"time":865000,"text":"We can't help but stop, right? This feeling's a wonderful thing. \n\n"},{"time":868000,"text":"It's the forever-always-on museum. \n\n"},{"time":871000,"text":"This is from the Cape last year. \n\n"},{"time":873000,"text":"I discovered that I had to find the equation of art and design, \n\n"},{"time":876000,"text":"which we know as circle-triangle-square. \n\n"},{"time":879000,"text":"It's everywhere on the beach, I discovered. \n\n"},{"time":881000,"text":"I began to collect every instance of circle-triangle-square. \n\n"},{"time":884000,"text":"I put these all back, by the way. \n\n"},{"time":886000,"text":"And I also discovered how .\n\n"},{"time":888000,"text":"some rocks are twins separated at birth."},{"time":891000,"text":"This is also out there, you know. \n\n"},{"time":894000,"text":"I'm, like, how did this happen, kind of thing? \n\n"},{"time":896000,"text":"I brought you guys together again. \n\n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":898000,"text":"So, three years ago I discovered, the letters M-I-T \n\n"},{"time":901000,"text":"occurring in simplicity and complexity. \n\n"},{"time":903000,"text":"My alma mater, MIT, and I had this moment -- \n\n"},{"time":905000,"text":"a kind of M. Night Shayamalan moment -- \n\n"},{"time":906000,"text":"where I thought, Whoa! I have to do this."},{"time":909000,"text":"And I went after it with passion. \n\n"},{"time":912000,"text":"However, recently this RISD opportunity kind of arose --\n\n"},{"time":916000,"text":"going to RISD -- and I couldn't reconcile this real easy, \n"},{"time":919000,"text":"because the letters had told me, MIT forever. \n\n"},{"time":923000,"text":"But I discovered in the French word raison d'Ãªtre. \n\n"},{"time":926000,"text":"I was, like, aha, wait a second. \n\n"},{"time":928000,"text":"And there RISD appeared. \n\n"},{"time":931000,"text":"And so I realized it was O.K. to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":933000,"text":"So, I'm going to RISD, actually. \n\n"},{"time":937000,"text":"Who's a RISD alum out there? \n\n"},{"time":939000,"text":"RISD alums? Yeah, RISD. There we go, RISD. Woo, RISD."},{"time":942000,"text":"I'm sorry, I'm sorry, Art Center -- Art Center is good, too."},{"time":944000,"text":"RISD is kind of my new kind of passion, \n\n"},{"time":948000,"text":"and I'll tell you a little bit about that. \n\n"},{"time":951000,"text":"So, RISD is -- \n\n"},{"time":953000,"text":"I was outside RISD,"},{"time":955000,"text":"and some student wrote this on some block, and I thought,\n\n"},{"time":957000,"text":"Wow, RISD wants to know what itself is. \n\n"},{"time":960000,"text":"And I have no idea what RISD should be, actually, \n\n"},{"time":962000,"text":"or what it wants to be, but one thing I have to tell you is that\n\n"},{"time":965000,"text":"although I'm a technologist, I don't like technology very much. \n\n"},{"time":968000,"text":"It's a, kind of, the qi thing, or whatever. \n\n"},{"time":970000,"text":"People say, \n"},{"time":972000,"text":"Are you going to bring RISD into the future?"},{"time":974000,"text":"And I say, well, I'm going to bring the future back to RISD. \n\n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":977000,"text":"There's my perspective. Because in reality, \n\n"},{"time":980000,"text":"the problem isn't how to make the world more technological. \n\n"},{"time":984000,"text":"It's about how to make it more humane again. \n\n"},{"time":986000,"text":"And if anything, I think RISD has a strange DNA. \n\n"},{"time":990000,"text":"It's a strange exuberance\n\n"},{"time":992000,"text":"about materials, about the world:"},{"time":994000,"text":"a fascination that I think the world needs \n\n"},{"time":996000,"text":"quite very much right now.\n"},{"time":998000,"text":"So, thank you everyone."}]}]}